1ebeb\" | [[Proto-Turkic language|Proto-Turkic]]\n|  rowspan=\"17\" bgcolor=\"#d6e1ec\" | [[Common Turkic languages|Common Turkic]]\n|  rowspan=\"4\" bgcolor=\"#e4e0f0\" style=\"border-left:none;\"| [[Oghuz languages|Southwestern Common Turkic (Oghuz)]]\n[[File:Oghuzlanguages6.png|upright=0.45|frameless]]\n|  colspan=\"2\" bgcolor=\"#e4e0f0\" style=\"border-right:none;\"| &nbsp;\n|\n* [[Pecheneg language|Pecheneg]] <small>(extinct)</small>\n|-\n|  colspan=\"2\" bgcolor=\"#f1e9df\" | West Oghuz\n|\n* [[Old Anatolian Turkish]] <small>(extinct)</small>\n* [[Ottoman Turkish language|Ottoman Turkish]] <small>(extinct)</small>\n* [[Turkish language|Turkish]]\n* [[Iraqi Turkmens#Language|Iraqi Turkmen]]\n* [[Gagauz language|Gagauz]]\n* [[Azerbaijani language|Azerbaijani]]\n* [[Balkan Gagauz Turkish language|Balkan Gagauz Turkish]]\n|-\n|  colspan=\"2\" bgcolor=\"#f1e9df\" | East Oghuz\n|\n* [[Turkmen language|Turkmen]]\n* [[Khorasani Turkic language|Khorasani Turkic]]\n|-\n|  colspan=\"2\" bgcolor=\"#f1e9df\" | South Oghuz\n|\n* [[Afshar language|Afshar]]\n* Dialects of Iran such as [[Qashqai language|Qashqai]], [[Sonqori language|Sonqori]], [[Aynallu language|Aynallu]], etc.\n|-\n|  bgcolor=\"#e4e0f0\" | (Arghu)\n|  colspan=\"2\" bgcolor=\"#e4e0f0\" | &nbsp;\n|\n* [[Khalaj language|Khalaj]]<ref>Khalaj is surrounded by Oghuz languages, but exhibits a number of features that classify it as non-Oghuz.</ref>\n|-\n|  rowspan=\"4\" bgcolor=\"#e4e0f0\" style=\"border-left:none;\"| [[Kypchak languages|Northwestern Common Turkic (Kipchak)]]\n[[File:Map-Kypchak Language World.png|upright=0.45|frameless]]\n|  colspan=\"2\" bgcolor=\"#e4e0f0\" style=\"border-right:none;\"| &nbsp;\n|\n* [[Kipchak language|Kipchak]] <small>(extinct)</small>\n|-\n|  colspan=\"2\" bgcolor=\"#f1e9df\" | West Kipchak\n|\n* [[Kumyk language|Kumyk]]\n* [[Karachay-Balkar language|Karachay-Balkar]]\n* [[Crimean Tatar language|Crimean Tatar]], [[Urum language|Urum]]<ref>Crimean Tatar and Urum are historically K